name: Swenson Hall, University of Wisconsin-Superior
directions: Every floor has both gendered restrooms and gender-neutral accessible single-stall restrooms.
comment: Sometimes open for long hours during the academic year; if it is late at night try multiple doors.

name: Crownhart Hall, University of Wisconsin-Superior
comment: The restrooms and showers on all resident floors (1,2, and 3) are gender neutral. Must be a resident and use a FOB to enter the building. The basement restrooms are gendered.

name: Walmart Supercenter
directions: In the back of the store between paint and hardware departments. The single family restroom is between two gendered restrooms.

name: Bleecker street cafe
comment: You have to be a customer

name: Portershed Café
directions: Just before the backdoor to the garden
comment: I don't think they would make you buy something if you ask nicely.

name: Grater Goods Deli/Café
directions: Left to the whine bar
comment: I don't believe they would make you buy something to use the restroom, but I'm there for the food. They are friendly people.

name: UPEI Student Union bathroom
directions: Go to second floor. Ask the secretary at the Student Union front desk if you can use the gender neutral bathroom

name: Emerald Bay Bar & Grill
comment: Gender neutral bathroom and women’s bathroom. “Inclusive” sign.

name: South Shore Bikes
comment: Bicycle shop

name: 4600 E County Line Rd, Indianapolis, IN 46237, USA
directions: Right next to the normal bathrooms, it’s a room with a locking door with one toilet labeled “family restroom”
comment: Not labeled as a unisex or gender neutral but it is a single toilet labeled family restroom so I definitely feel way more comfortable using this!

name: Chan's Kitchen
comment: Parking is easy and the food is good. It's real-deal Taiwanese food!

name: University of New Hampshire at Manchester
directions: Fourth Floor. It is left down the hallway a bit. It is labelled.

name: Drake Memorial Library
directions: Gender neutral on ground floor tower 2. Gender neutral with changing table main floor tower 2. Other gendered restrooms are accessible.
comment: Open to the public.

name: CPISB
directions: Bathrooms located in office hallway breakrooms (southwest side of the building)
comment: Office wing is open from 8:00-17:00 Monday - Friday

name: Haven Books and Cafe
directions: At the back of the store, beside the cafe.
comment: Run by the Carleton student union. The staff are fairly accommodating.

name: Franktown Market
directions: Back to the right hand corner

name: Grounds for sculpture
directions: Base of tower by pound

name: Lovejoy Library Family Restroom.
directions: 1st floor, directly left as you enter from the quad
comment: Has a chair and a handicap accessible toilet.

name: Dunkin
comment: It's okay to use the restroom without being a customer.

name: MUC Dining Services Locker Room
directions: In the basement of the MUC. Easily accessible via the main entrance elevator, but also accessible from the cafeteria. Just take the elevator down, then turn right. It's on the right at the end of the hall.
comment: Primarily for SIUE Dining Services employees, but you don't need a code or anything to use them and I've never been stopped for any reason. There are 2 locking unisex bathrooms with working showers and biohazard disposal containers. The one on the right has a paid menstrual product dispensor.

name: Goshen Brewing Company
comment: Marked “all gender”- has three restrooms, one with a changing table.

name: Pentacle Coffee
directions: Back of the coffee shop

name: Starbucks
directions: go in the Starbucks and ask for the restroom code

name: Starbucks/UNG
directions: Same floor as Starbucks (across Suntrust bank). 2nd floor total.
comment:
Hours are 6 AM to 9 PM on Monday through Thursday.
6 AM to 7 PM on Friday.
7 AM to 7 PM on Saturday.
7 AM to 8 PM on Sunday.

These 2, single stall restrooms are available to students and the general public.

name: Learning Services Building
directions: One on each floor in the hallway before the stairs. The second one requires a key, which usually the secretary will give you, if you ask. Open generally 9-5 during the weekdays.

name: Los Olivos Commons, Pomona, CA 91768, USA
Caliber Coffee Co.
directions: Through the door and around to the right. Two unisex single stall restrooms, one accessible, no changing tables.

name: Barnwood McDonald's
directions: At the back to the left as you go in
comment: Disabled access toilet can be used as gender natural you don't have to be a paying customer

name: 3211 Providence Dr, Anchorage, AK 99508, USA
directions: 1st 2nd and 3rd floor of UAA consortium library has “family restroom” across from elevators by standard restrooms.
comment: Doors are usually locked you must ask an attendant and they’ll unlock it. Sometimes they’re open already though.

name: Huset
directions: Jus before the elevator, take a right then the toilet should be on the right.

name: Belk Gym Rooms 016 A&B
directions: From the main entrance: turn left and walk by the basketball court until you get to a set of stairs on your left. Go down them to the ground floor, then turn left and walk past room 008 (on your right) and 010 (on your left). Make the first right after 008 down a long hall. Once you reach the end of the hall, turn left. Make another left into a hallway across from room 017 (on your right), and the restrooms will be on your left. If you reach room 014B or 013B, you've gone too far.
comment: Going to Belk gym requires either being a student at UNC Charlotte or paying a membership fee ($25). They do have staff manning the front desk at all times and wandering around the building. They will be happy to show you the way.

name: Doc Bryan
directions: First floor, across the hall from the health and wellness center.

name: Woodward Hall Room 245B
directions:
From the main entrance on the first floor (facing athletic fields): head left until you reach room 140, and go up the stairs to the second floor. Exit the stairwell, go through the doors on your right, turn right down the hallway, and turn right again to continue down the hallway. 245B will be just ahead on your right. If you reach rooms 250+, you've gone too far.
From the main entrance on the second floor (facing the eagle statue and the College of Health and Human Services): make the first right and continue down the hallway. Take a left, then take the first right to continue down the hallway. Continue straight for a bit (you will pass a building exit on your right), then turn right again to continue down the hallway. 245B will be just ahead on your right. If you reach rooms 250+, you've gone too far.

name: Comstock Hall
directions: First floor to your right, might need a Ucard to get through the door. Also one in the dining area

name: College of Health and Human Services Room 110
directions: On the first floor. From any of the main entrances (those facing the courtyard with benches and the Cato College of Education): turn left onto the first hallway and walk north (in the direction of the Popp-Martin Student Union). You will eventually pass a wood-paneled staircase and elevators on the right, then rooms 103 and 109 on your left. Turn right down the hallway after room 109, and room 110 will be the first room on your right. If you reach rooms 116, 117, or 120, you've gone too far. There are also building maps on the walls in several locations incase you get lost.

name: Loblolly Creamery
directions: To the back between the yellow walls.
comment: There are two gender neutral bathrooms, the one to the right has a changing table. The staff is also VERY friendly to the LGBTQ community, and many are members themselves.

name: MYLO COFFEE CO
directions: All the way to the back on the right side.
comment: The back is secluded so no one should see you. Just walk straight back without approaching the bar and people won’t pay attention to you.

name: McEniry 122A
directions:
On the first floor.
From the left side of the building: walk past lecture halls 124 and 123. On your left, immediately after the exit, you will see 122A. If you get to lecture halls 117 or 118, you've gone too far.
From the right side of the building: walk past lecture halls 117 and 118. On the right, you will see 117, 122, then 122A. If you reach the exit or rooms 124 or 123, you've gone too far.

name: Popp-Martin Student Union
directions: Rooms 164 A and B. Starting at the main entrance, go down the second hallway on the right. The bathrooms are right next to the entrance to the Movie Theater.
comment: If you can't find them, there is always someone at the info desk in the rotunda who can help you. Building hours are 7AM-1AM M-F, 9AM-1AM Sat/Sun during the regular fall and spring semesters. Hours are reduced during holidays and the summer semester.

name: Taft Public Library
directions: 2 unisex bathrooms, 1 on each floor
comment: Check hours on website

name: Mendon Town Hall
directions: Bathrooms on all 3 floors of town hall. Basement is near the side door, 1st floor is in the back at the end of the hall by the elevator, 2nd floor is in the back hall through the meeting room to the right of the stage.
comment: Basement and 2nd floor have unisex single user bathrooms, 1st floor has seperate single user gendered bathrooms.

name: Mendon Town Beach
comment:
Beach charges admission but you can ask to just use the bathrooms. 
 Seasonal facility (open June-Aug). Single stall gendered bathrooms  and 3rd  single stall gender neutral/accessible batbroom

name: Boone High School
comment: If you are a transgender student, you can request to use the teacher restrooms via principal Byam.

name: West Kentucky tech
directions: The restrooms are all over the campus there's at least one in every building

name: West Village Dining Commons
directions: First floor near service desk, there are two single-stall unisex bathrooms

name: Student Center Gender Neutral
directions: Third floor, between the printer and the vending machines. Next to the women’s bathroom.

name: Metal
directions: Straight through the electric doors and in front and to the right(signposted)

name: LightBox Cafe
directions: Walk in and turn right, or just ask for the toilets~
comment: Don’t have to be a customer but the staff are lovely and the food is great so definitely stay if you can~

name: SUNY POLY - Kunsela Hall
directions: Bottom floor, all the way down the hall towards IT department.
comment: Does get used a lot but is a perfect all-gender restroom.

name: Calle José Ballester Gozalvo, 37, 46011 Valencia, Spain
Calle José Ballester Gozalvo, 41, 46011 Valencia, Spain
Carrer del Portal de Valldigna, 6, 46003 València, Valencia, Spain
Carrer de Martí Grajales, 17 Bajo, 46011 València, Valencia, Spain
Carrer del Baró de San Petrillo, 13, 46020 València, Valencia, Spain
street: Carrer del Baró de San Petrillo

name: Target
directions: Located in the front of Target next to the entrance and guest service.
comment: There's a family restroom in the restroom area here. Target is also pro LGBT so using the standard restrooms may be fine too if conditions warrant it.

name: Regal Grand Esplanade 14
directions: Located in the lobby of the movie theater next to the bar in the left.
comment: No ticket needed to use the restroom, just let the ticket taker know you need to use it and they'll point you in that direction.

name: Moose coffee
directions: Small single toilet to the left of the kitchen

name: Alex
directions: Enter the Merchant Venturer's building, head straight ahead, turn left before the stairs past the chairs. Keep going forward and turn left. Go forward and look on your left.
comment: This is a university building but you should be able to enter and leave without any problems. Just be confident.

name: Walmart
directions: As of September 2019 there’s a family restroom in the back behind electronics, right next to the gendered bathrooms!

name: James Center Starbucks
directions: When you enter walk straight in past the counter to your left, and they'll be in front of you. Two single stall all-gender restrooms.
comment: As of 9/9/19 there is no code or keypad on these :)

name: Washington State Convention Center
directions: Two small restrooms on the 4th floor and one large restroom (two formerly gendered restrooms combined) on the 6th floor.
comment: Available to convention attendees (I’ve used them for Sakura-con for the past three years). Unsure about the availability for the general public.

name: Fiamma Burger
comment: One single-person restroom; not gendered.

name: Pier 1 imports
directions: Back of the store to the right
comment: Don’t have to be paying customer, just browse

name: REI
directions: Back left corner of the store by customer service
comment: Don’t have to be paying customer

name: Notre dame de Namur university
directions: There’s a gender neutral bathroom in saint marys hall near the registrar and at civilly hall bottom floor. There are probly more in other building but those are the only ones I’ve had classes in
comment: It’s a university? So if not a student just park in the visitor spots in the main lot. Saint Mary’s should be straight ahead I doubt anyone will bother you- you could be coming in to apply, they wouldn’t know.

name: University Church
directions: Gender neutral bath

name: D hall
directions: To the right after entering
comment: Must swipe into the dining hall

name: Harper Memorial Library
directions: Large accessible single user restroom on west side of the first floor. There are also three single user restrooms on the third floor near Harper Café (take the east staircase).
comment: The third floor bathrooms often have a long line, and you might have a hard time getting into the building on Saturdays.

name: Popovers on the Square
directions: Back left
comment: Overall a friendly environment

name: Short sands beach
directions: In bathhouse, multiple gender neutral bathrooms with changing tables and sharps containers

name: Seeley G. Muddy Building
directions: On the first floor basement next to the lab store.

name: Whitaker Lab
directions: Third floor across the bridge from the lobby.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the door, follow the left wall.
comment: You can use it without buying anything.

name: HEB
directions: It's at the center of the wall you enter from. If you enter from the left, go right. If you enter from the right, go left.

name: GTM
directions: Turn right after the glass cases when you enter
comment: Act like you are browsing for a bit. You need to get checked in

name: Hawk and Pony
directions: In the back
comment: Previously Arbor Cafe, same single stall bathroom goodness

name: 70 Daesin-dong, Seodaemun-gu, Seoul, South Korea
directions: As you enter global hall take first right

name: Blog 167
directions:
Third floor lobby is a gender neutral multiple occupancy bathroom (though some people lock the main door).
2nd floor has a single occupancy gender neutral bathroom.
comment: Don't know if this will help since it's on federal property and thus not accessible to most, but it's something I wish I'd known months ago (and maybe it can help one person)

name: George Moore Building, Glasgow G4 0BA, UK
directions: On the right as you exit the lifts in the centre of the building (in front and to the left from the stairwell) - access this lift from the canteen on the ground floor.
comment: Two single-stall rooms featuring male and female signage.

name: 6661 Sooke Rd, Sooke, BC V9Z 0A1, Canada
directions: Far wall past the bakery department.

name: Venable Hall
directions: On the ground floor of Venable Hall, by Kenan Science Library. It is on the same side as the womans bathroom it is the door right beyond the opening. If needing accessible elevator enter through Murray hall by BeAM take the elevator down and go to the left. Then the next left.

name: The Hub @ UWS
directions: Next to the lift, turn left and it's first on your right.
comment: That particular room isn't often used but the surrounding area can get busy.

name: Dreambuilders Op Shop
directions: Out the back through the cafe either enter from the store or from the side door near the car park
comment: 3 toilets with various levels of privacy but are all gender neutral. A shower is also available is required.
